1
00:00:05,120 --> 00:00:08,039
We’ll just be nothing
more than an engaged couple.

2
00:00:08,080 --> 00:00:10,960
I’ll renew the contract year by year only.

3
00:00:11,240 --> 00:00:12,640
Everyone’s going out to celebrate.

4
00:00:12,680 --> 00:00:14,040
Without me?

5
00:00:14,080 --> 00:00:16,000
I’m the one who made this happen.

6
00:00:16,040 --> 00:00:18,200
Are you okay?
Why did you stop the car here?

7
00:00:18,240 --> 00:00:20,440
I’m sleepy.

8
00:00:20,880 --> 00:00:24,320
You keep moving the seat up
and down, I’m getting dizzy.

9
00:00:24,360 --> 00:00:26,160
You want me to sleep with you?

10
00:00:26,880 --> 00:00:29,440
Or do you want to sleep in the guest room?

11
00:00:29,520 --> 00:00:32,479
Don’t even think about doing anything to me.

12
00:00:32,479 --> 00:00:34,120
I do Muay Thai, just so you know.

13
00:00:34,120 --> 00:00:35,800
I’ll elbow you, seriously.

14
00:00:36,240 --> 00:00:37,640
Are you going to sleep or not?

15
00:00:38,640 --> 00:00:40,640
Then turn off the light.

16
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:06,880
Everyone’s going out to celebrate.

17
00:01:06,920 --> 00:01:08,440
Without me?

18
00:01:09,720 --> 00:01:11,840
I’m the one who made this happen.

19
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:13,560
I know.

20
00:01:13,640 --> 00:01:16,360
that I’m the one no one in this family wants.

21
00:01:17,240 --> 00:01:19,440
But I didn’t think Dad, Mom, and Song

22
00:01:19,560 --> 00:01:21,560
would hate me this much.

23
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:35,360
Si.

24
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:37,560
What’s wrong?

25
00:01:37,960 --> 00:01:39,560
Why are you crying?

26
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:56,840
What’s wrong with you?

27
00:01:57,160 --> 00:01:58,960
You can tell me.

28
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:04,040
Today.

29
00:02:04,880 --> 00:02:07,360
I just had a fight with my family.

30
00:02:08,919 --> 00:02:11,640
Everyone thinks I’m the problem.

31
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,360
You know.

32
00:02:18,040 --> 00:02:20,880
Today they went out to celebrate together.

33
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:23,560
That you agreed to renew the land lease.

34
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:28,640
But they didn’t invite me at all.

35
00:02:33,079 --> 00:02:35,640
They’re afraid I’ll cause trouble again.

36
00:02:37,960 --> 00:02:39,560
Why?

37
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:44,520
Why does no one see my worth?

38
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:47,760
Even though I’m the one who made this happen.

39
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:03,160
When I was a kid.

40
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:06,560
Whenever I threw a tantrum.

41
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:09,480
My dad used to do this.

42
00:03:10,520 --> 00:03:12,160
And then he’d hug me.

43
00:03:12,920 --> 00:03:14,640
To make me stop crying.

44
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:22,160
Saying something like that.

45
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:25,120
You want me to turn around and hug you, right?

46
00:03:25,480 --> 00:03:26,640
Dream on.

47
00:03:31,640 --> 00:03:32,760
Si.

48
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:36,040
I don’t want to see you cry.

49
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:38,640
You.

50
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:40,880
You don’t suit crying at all.

51
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:43,840
When you cry.

52
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:46,560
You’re not pretty at all, you know?

53
00:03:57,079 --> 00:03:58,360
Really?

54
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:01,560
Is it that ugly?

55
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:03,840
Mm.

56
00:04:04,200 --> 00:04:05,760
Very ugly.

57
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:16,560
If you don’t want to see.

58
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:18,560
Then turn around.

59
00:04:21,560 --> 00:04:23,720
That’s not what I meant.

60
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:26,960
I don’t want to be the kind of person...

61
00:04:27,520 --> 00:04:29,240
who turns their back on you.

62
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:39,360
I told you to turn around, so just do it.

63
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:41,159
Turn around.

64
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:45,040
Just turn.

65
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:15,600
♪The melon farm girl from Suphan.♪

66
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:18,280
♪Her name is known far and wide.♪

67
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:21,880
♪Famous all across the city.♪

68
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:24,320
Because she joined.

69
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:26,920
The rising melon goddess contest.

70
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:29,760
Her image reached the capital.

71
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:32,880
And she rose into the spotlight.

72
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:38,840
The melon girl changes her fate.

73
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:01,480
Quiet.

74
00:09:02,640 --> 00:09:05,280
You keep making noise, I’m trying to sleep.

75
00:09:06,920 --> 00:09:08,240
You stupid chicken.

76
00:09:10,040 --> 00:09:11,040
Turn off the music.

77
00:09:11,080 --> 00:09:12,720
And take this chicken away.

78
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:15,560
Or I’ll snap its neck and grill it.

79
00:09:15,560 --> 00:09:16,640
Just watch me.

80
00:09:48,840 --> 00:09:50,440
I just realized...

81
00:09:50,640 --> 00:09:52,560
I’m weak to a woman’s tears.

82
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:56,560
I’ll make sure you won’t cry again.

83
00:09:57,320 --> 00:09:59,040
Trust me, Si.

84
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:45,800
You damn tapeworm.

85
00:10:45,840 --> 00:10:47,160
What are you eating?

86
00:10:47,720 --> 00:10:49,160
It’s grilled chicken.

87
00:10:58,080 --> 00:10:59,120
You want some?

88
00:10:59,120 --> 00:11:01,480
Want it? I’ll get you some, come on.

89
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:02,840
You eat it yourself.

90
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:15,440
Jon.

91
00:11:17,040 --> 00:11:18,240
Jon.

92
00:11:19,640 --> 00:11:20,960
Jon.

93
00:11:21,520 --> 00:11:22,760
Jon.

94
00:11:25,800 --> 00:11:27,480
You damn tapeworm.

95
00:11:27,920 --> 00:11:29,360
Where did Jon go?

96
00:11:29,680 --> 00:11:31,240
What about your brother?

97
00:11:31,280 --> 00:11:33,200
Hey, where are you taking Jon?

98
00:11:33,240 --> 00:11:34,880
I’m taking him to my place.

99
00:11:34,920 --> 00:11:37,440
Si got annoyed by it crowing this morning.

100
00:11:38,120 --> 00:11:39,160
Last night.

101
00:11:39,280 --> 00:11:41,760
Parrot lady slept here with you?

102
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:43,120
Yeah.

103
00:11:43,520 --> 00:11:45,160
Got a problem with that?

104
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:47,760
Who would dare? No problem at all.

105
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:50,080
Oh right, bro.

106
00:11:50,080 --> 00:11:51,840
I’ve been wondering for days.

107
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:54,080
But I didn’t dare ask.

108
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:57,240
Is Parrot lady your girlfriend?

109
00:11:58,760 --> 00:11:59,760
Yeah.

110
00:11:59,760 --> 00:12:02,560
Come on, bro, that was way too quick.

111
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:04,640
If you’re sure about it.

112
00:12:04,680 --> 00:12:06,080
Why hesitate?

113
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:08,960
So when did you fall for Parrot lady?

114
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:10,480
I had no idea.

115
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,760
Love at first sight.

116
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:14,360
You know it?

117
00:12:15,320 --> 00:12:17,120
Love at first sight, huh.

118
00:12:17,160 --> 00:12:19,560
You’re amazing, bro. High five.

119
00:12:21,040 --> 00:12:23,760
Awesome. So sweet.

120
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:25,120
From now on.

121
00:12:25,120 --> 00:12:27,360
You better treat Si well too.

122
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:29,760
Love her like you love me.

123
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:30,800
I’m off.

124
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:34,040
There’s food in the house, go ahead and eat.

125
00:12:34,080 --> 00:12:35,360
But keep it quiet.

126
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:36,760
She might wake up.

127
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:38,240
Got it.

128
00:12:42,640 --> 00:12:43,960
Jon.

129
00:12:44,560 --> 00:12:47,840
Jon, I’m sorry. I didn’t mean to.

130
00:12:47,880 --> 00:12:50,680
A chicken like you shouldn’t have died so soon.

131
00:12:52,560 --> 00:12:55,960
You idiot, why did you eat Jon?

132
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:57,600
I didn’t mean to.

133
00:12:57,640 --> 00:12:59,040
I didn’t know.

134
00:13:02,760 --> 00:13:05,280
Are you serious?

135
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:09,960
All the rice I’ve been feeding you all this time.

136
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,920
You idiot.

137
00:13:16,640 --> 00:13:19,120
-I’m sorry.
-Jiw.

138
00:13:20,120 --> 00:13:21,560
Why are you crying?

139
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:24,960
Si.

140
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:27,240
I’ll put the dishes away first, bro.

141
00:13:27,280 --> 00:13:29,120
Ask your girlfriend yourself.

142
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:35,240
That damn tapeworm
was sitting there eating chicken.

143
00:13:35,280 --> 00:13:37,120
So I asked where Jon went.

144
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:39,640
And he just started crying.

145
00:13:40,640 --> 00:13:43,520
I just said I was annoyed by it this morning.

146
00:13:43,560 --> 00:13:46,200
Why did you have to kill it?

147
00:13:46,240 --> 00:13:48,360
How can you be so heartless?

148
00:13:48,880 --> 00:13:51,120
You got tricked.

149
00:13:51,160 --> 00:13:53,880
I just took Jon to leave at my brother’s place.

150
00:13:53,960 --> 00:13:56,760
Because I saw you were annoyed
by it crowing this morning.

151
00:14:02,920 --> 00:14:05,840
Parrot lady got tricked by me.

152
00:14:09,680 --> 00:14:10,880
You.

153
00:14:10,920 --> 00:14:12,760
Then why didn’t you tell me?

154
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:22,880
And just now.

155
00:14:23,640 --> 00:14:26,080
I heard that damn tapeworm call me.

156
00:14:26,120 --> 00:14:27,760
your girlfriend.

157
00:14:28,160 --> 00:14:30,160
How does he know about us?

158
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:32,440
Well, we are a couple now.

159
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:34,560
No.

160
00:14:34,760 --> 00:14:36,440
We’re more than that.

161
00:14:36,680 --> 00:14:37,680
Because...

162
00:14:37,680 --> 00:14:40,640
we’re engaged.

163
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:44,720
I think...

164
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:47,360
you’re skipping steps a bit.

165
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:54,480
What are you doing?

166
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:58,040
You cried all night, your eyes are swollen.

167
00:15:01,640 --> 00:15:03,160
It’s okay.

168
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:05,040
It’ll go away.

169
00:15:05,520 --> 00:15:07,440
I’ll get something to put on your eyes.

170
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:09,400
And...

171
00:15:09,640 --> 00:15:11,640
do you feel better now?

172
00:15:12,840 --> 00:15:14,320
I’m worried about you.

173
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:17,560
What’s wrong with you?

174
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:20,080
Are you crazy?

175
00:15:20,080 --> 00:15:21,680
Are you possessed or what?

176
00:15:21,680 --> 00:15:24,240
Why are you suddenly being
so sweet this morning?

177
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:26,000
Or...

178
00:15:26,760 --> 00:15:28,040
Do you have a fever?

179
00:15:33,760 --> 00:15:34,960
Actually.

180
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,840
I’ve been good to you
since the first day we met.

181
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:40,040
You just didn’t notice.

182
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:41,800
So I decided...

183
00:15:41,800 --> 00:15:44,160
to treat you even better.

184
00:15:44,640 --> 00:15:45,640
Maybe then.

185
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:47,840
you’ll finally see me.

186
00:15:53,760 --> 00:15:54,760
Oh please.

187
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:58,040
You two are both crazy, boss and subordinate.

188
00:16:02,120 --> 00:16:03,120
Wait.

189
00:16:03,240 --> 00:16:04,360
Where are you going?

190
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:07,160
I’m going back home.

191
00:16:07,280 --> 00:16:08,280
I’m heading off.

192
00:16:08,320 --> 00:16:09,320
Bye.

193
00:16:12,960 --> 00:16:14,440
The shirt you’re wearing.

194
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:16,160
Wash it and return it to me.

195
00:16:16,280 --> 00:16:17,880
Don’t just keep it.

196
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:22,360
Jiw.

197
00:16:32,880 --> 00:16:34,440
Hello, Si.

198
00:16:52,280 --> 00:16:53,720
What’s up?

199
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:57,600
The thing I asked you to handle.

200
00:16:57,640 --> 00:16:58,960
Is it all done?

201
00:16:58,960 --> 00:17:01,080
All done. Completely taken care of.

202
00:17:05,440 --> 00:17:06,960
(Sujintra Thanyakannareerat)

203
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:09,560
I told you to pack all my personal belongings.

204
00:17:09,839 --> 00:17:11,160
Why isn’t it finished yet?

205
00:17:12,720 --> 00:17:14,000
It’s already done.

206
00:17:14,040 --> 00:17:15,880
Actually, it’s been done for a while.

207
00:17:15,880 --> 00:17:18,440
This is all you have, Si.

208
00:17:21,359 --> 00:17:24,720
Normally, you don’t really work anyway.

209
00:17:24,760 --> 00:17:26,880
So you don’t have many documents.

210
00:17:30,920 --> 00:17:33,160
Have someone move my things to my car.

211
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:40,040
You don’t trust me.

212
00:17:40,080 --> 00:17:42,920
You even had someone follow me around?

213
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:45,040
Why?

214
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:47,480
Afraid I’ll steal company property?

215
00:17:48,960 --> 00:17:50,560
Not at all, Si.

216
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:52,960
I’m just worried.

217
00:17:53,240 --> 00:17:55,000
Where did you stay last night?

218
00:17:55,040 --> 00:17:56,680
Why didn’t you come home?

219
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:00,840
That’s my business.

220
00:18:04,240 --> 00:18:07,120
Then why did you have staff pack your things?

221
00:18:07,160 --> 00:18:08,560
Where are you going?

222
00:18:09,760 --> 00:18:11,960
I can see you really want to be CEO.

223
00:18:12,520 --> 00:18:14,440
So I’m stepping aside for you.

224
00:18:15,360 --> 00:18:17,560
And tell Dad and Mom for me.

225
00:18:18,480 --> 00:18:20,440
I won’t set foot here again.

226
00:18:20,680 --> 00:18:22,040
If they dislike me that much.

227
00:18:22,080 --> 00:18:24,440
Then I’ll stay out of everyone’s sight.

228
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:26,480
Wait, Si.

229
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:30,480
I just want you to understand.

230
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:32,840
We’re sisters.

231
00:18:33,560 --> 00:18:36,160
I never wanted that position.

232
00:18:37,440 --> 00:18:39,560
Please come back to work.

233
00:18:40,240 --> 00:18:43,040
Let’s take care of
our parents’ company together.

234
00:18:47,240 --> 00:18:48,360
You know.

235
00:18:50,840 --> 00:18:53,160
You shouldn’t have been born as my sister.

236
00:18:55,320 --> 00:18:56,960
I was better off as an only child.

237
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:58,760
Why were you even born?

238
00:19:17,280 --> 00:19:18,440
Song.

239
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:20,560
What’s wrong?

240
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:28,160
Why are you crying?

241
00:19:31,240 --> 00:19:34,160
Si packed her things and left the company.

242
00:19:34,520 --> 00:19:36,440
She said she won’t come back.

243
00:19:36,720 --> 00:19:38,440
She only causes trouble every day.

244
00:19:38,680 --> 00:19:40,120
I’ll call and handle it.

245
00:19:40,160 --> 00:19:41,760
Don’t call, Dad.

246
00:19:42,680 --> 00:19:45,560
She already hates me enough as it is.

247
00:19:49,280 --> 00:19:50,960
Don’t overthink it.

248
00:19:52,040 --> 00:19:53,560
That’s just how she is.

249
00:19:53,600 --> 00:19:55,560
She’ll come back once she cools down.

250
00:19:56,640 --> 00:19:57,960
Dad.

251
00:19:58,160 --> 00:20:01,040
Can you give her the CEO position?

252
00:20:01,520 --> 00:20:03,920
I’ll take care of her myself.

253
00:20:05,680 --> 00:20:08,480
I don’t want her to think you’re biased.

254
00:20:08,520 --> 00:20:10,560
Or that you love us differently.

255
00:20:11,760 --> 00:20:14,040
You know I’m not like that.

256
00:20:15,320 --> 00:20:18,760
But what you did made her think that.

257
00:20:20,320 --> 00:20:22,040
Song, listen to me.

258
00:20:22,600 --> 00:20:24,920
I’ve always believed.

259
00:20:24,960 --> 00:20:26,680
that I love both my daughters equally.

260
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:31,080
But I just realized
I barely need to worry about you.

261
00:20:31,320 --> 00:20:33,760
Because you can take care of yourself.

262
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:36,960
I worry more about your sister.

263
00:20:37,720 --> 00:20:39,640
If one day your mom and I are gone.

264
00:20:39,680 --> 00:20:40,960
How will she live?

265
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:44,960
If anyone’s at fault,
it’s us for raising her this way.

266
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:49,960
But you didn’t have to be so harsh with her.

267
00:20:50,240 --> 00:20:51,960
I’ve tried everything.

268
00:20:51,960 --> 00:20:54,040
Both soft and tough approaches.

269
00:20:54,160 --> 00:20:56,240
She hasn’t changed at all.

270
00:20:56,560 --> 00:20:58,040
What do you want me to do?

271
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:01,960
I’ll try to help you.

272
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:07,680
If we still can’t change her behavior.

273
00:21:09,880 --> 00:21:11,480
Can you promise me?

274
00:21:12,360 --> 00:21:14,560
that you’ll take care of your sister.

275
00:21:15,520 --> 00:21:17,640
No matter how reckless she is.

276
00:21:19,680 --> 00:21:20,960
Okay, Dad.

277
00:21:21,240 --> 00:21:22,960
Don’t worry.

278
00:21:23,440 --> 00:21:25,520
I’ll take care of her.

279
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:34,960
Uncle Kamnan, have some water.

280
00:21:35,560 --> 00:21:37,360
Thanks, Klao.

281
00:21:42,560 --> 00:21:43,840
That’s refreshing.

282
00:21:44,840 --> 00:21:46,520
By the way.

283
00:21:46,560 --> 00:21:47,960
Is something wrong?

284
00:21:48,120 --> 00:21:49,400
You had Jiw.

285
00:21:49,440 --> 00:21:50,640
come get me.

286
00:21:52,160 --> 00:21:54,680
About what we talked about...

287
00:21:54,720 --> 00:21:58,680
I wanted you to take care of
the agricultural learning center in Bangkok.

288
00:21:59,120 --> 00:22:00,440
But I think...

289
00:22:00,480 --> 00:22:02,760
that project has to be put on hold.

290
00:22:03,640 --> 00:22:07,080
Because I renewed the land lease
with the mall.

291
00:22:07,640 --> 00:22:08,760
Oh, really?

292
00:22:09,640 --> 00:22:10,840
That’s a shame.

293
00:22:10,960 --> 00:22:12,000
You said before.

294
00:22:12,040 --> 00:22:14,480
you wanted teenagers to come learn.

295
00:22:14,760 --> 00:22:18,040
So kids these days would
value agriculture more.

296
00:22:20,520 --> 00:22:22,160
I’m really sorry.

297
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:24,000
It’s okay.

298
00:22:24,040 --> 00:22:26,360
Klao, why are you apologizing to me?

299
00:22:26,440 --> 00:22:27,440
It’s okay.

300
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:30,760
But I promise.

301
00:22:31,120 --> 00:22:33,320
One day, I will.

302
00:22:33,360 --> 00:22:35,560
make this project succeed.

303
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:37,480
Alright.

304
00:22:37,640 --> 00:22:39,040
You damn tapeworm.

305
00:22:39,080 --> 00:22:42,080
Where are you?
Come help me carry my bags.

306
00:22:42,080 --> 00:22:43,880
Hurry, I’m hot.

307
00:22:43,920 --> 00:22:45,280
Coming, sis.

308
00:22:45,320 --> 00:22:48,200
You’re shouting so loud, Parrot lady.

309
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:51,000
He’s talking to the village head.

310
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:52,720
How would I know?

311
00:22:53,600 --> 00:22:55,440
-Hey.
-What do you want me to do?

312
00:22:55,880 --> 00:22:57,360
Here’s your pay.

313
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:59,400
Carry my bags into the house.

314
00:22:59,440 --> 00:23:01,440
Carry them, don’t drag them.

315
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:03,600
Each of my bags costs tens of thousands.
They’ll get scratched.

316
00:23:03,600 --> 00:23:06,320
Each bag costs ten thousand,
and you’re paying me a hundred?

317
00:23:06,840 --> 00:23:09,440
I usually charge two hundred.

318
00:23:10,360 --> 00:23:12,760
Ever heard of half-half plus?

319
00:23:12,760 --> 00:23:14,080
So stingy.

320
00:23:14,120 --> 00:23:16,080
-Take it or leave it.
-I’ll take it.

321
00:23:16,120 --> 00:23:19,120
Since you’re my brother’s girlfriend,
I’ll do it.

322
00:23:20,080 --> 00:23:21,680
How nice.

323
00:23:21,720 --> 00:23:22,800
You brat.

324
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:24,440
What?

325
00:23:25,840 --> 00:23:28,400
-Carry them carefully.
-Yeah, yeah.

326
00:23:29,680 --> 00:23:31,520
I’ve seen this before.

327
00:23:31,560 --> 00:23:33,440
Selling at Rong Kluea for two hundred.

328
00:23:33,480 --> 00:23:35,120
You damn idiot, you dumbass.

329
00:23:35,560 --> 00:23:37,240
You talk too much.

330
00:23:39,760 --> 00:23:41,320
What bag is that?

331
00:23:42,920 --> 00:23:44,840
It’s my clothes.

332
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:47,840
I’m sick of my house, so I’m staying here for...

333
00:23:47,880 --> 00:23:49,400
a couple of nights.

334
00:23:49,520 --> 00:23:52,720
As your fiancée,
I don’t need your permission, right?

335
00:23:53,840 --> 00:23:55,520
Stay as long as you want.

336
00:23:56,680 --> 00:24:00,160
Great, I can relax here then.

337
00:24:09,240 --> 00:24:10,520
Jiw.

338
00:24:10,560 --> 00:24:12,640
Can I have some water? I’m hot.

339
00:24:17,360 --> 00:24:18,520
Water?

340
00:24:19,880 --> 00:24:22,920
Uh... there’s no running water tonight.

341
00:24:22,960 --> 00:24:24,960
What? No water?

342
00:24:24,960 --> 00:24:27,120
So how am I supposed to bathe?

343
00:24:27,720 --> 00:24:29,560
It’s like this here.

344
00:24:29,600 --> 00:24:30,960
Water goes out often.

345
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:32,520
I usually bathe here.

346
00:24:32,520 --> 00:24:33,600
Are you crazy?

347
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:35,880
You want me to strip naked outside?

348
00:24:35,920 --> 00:24:37,360
Right here?

349
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:39,080
No way, I’m shy.

350
00:24:39,120 --> 00:24:40,360
Who are you shy around?

351
00:24:40,360 --> 00:24:42,440
It’s just the two of us here.

352
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:44,600
If there is, then...

353
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:49,920
Don’t say that, I’m already scared.

354
00:24:52,280 --> 00:24:53,880
I meant Pao.

355
00:24:53,920 --> 00:24:55,600
Are you shy in front of a cat?

356
00:24:56,160 --> 00:24:58,120
Pao is sleeping inside.

357
00:24:58,160 --> 00:25:00,120
It won’t come out to peek at me.

358
00:25:02,480 --> 00:25:04,800
How about this, if you’re shy.

359
00:25:05,160 --> 00:25:06,520
Just wear a sarong.

360
00:25:14,520 --> 00:25:16,000
A sarong?

361
00:25:16,960 --> 00:25:18,400
How do I wear it?

362
00:25:19,160 --> 00:25:21,840
Here, step into the middle.

363
00:25:23,200 --> 00:25:24,600
Put your legs in.

364
00:25:28,080 --> 00:25:29,840
Then take off your clothes.

365
00:25:30,920 --> 00:25:32,440
Then turn around.

366
00:25:32,480 --> 00:25:35,720
Close your eyes too,
don’t look at me naked, got it?

367
00:25:37,960 --> 00:25:39,040
Hey.

368
00:25:39,520 --> 00:25:41,440
Hold it properly.

369
00:25:45,560 --> 00:25:46,440
Are you done yet?

370
00:25:46,440 --> 00:25:47,840
Not yet!

371
00:25:50,760 --> 00:25:51,320
Hey.

372
00:25:51,400 --> 00:25:52,240
You pervert.

373
00:25:52,880 --> 00:25:54,400
You’re too slow.

374
00:25:54,400 --> 00:25:57,280
Hold on. Didn’t you say you wouldn’t peek at me?

375
00:26:08,800 --> 00:26:11,160
Hey, I told you not to peek.

376
00:26:11,880 --> 00:26:13,640
Like I’d want to look.

377
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:16,080
You were peeking, I saw you.

378
00:26:25,160 --> 00:26:26,960
What do I do next?

379
00:26:27,320 --> 00:26:29,840
Can I turn around now?

380
00:26:30,800 --> 00:26:32,560
You can turn now.

381
00:26:32,560 --> 00:26:34,160
But don’t peek.

382
00:26:39,560 --> 00:26:40,720
You pervert.

383
00:26:41,520 --> 00:26:42,840
Sorry, sorry.

384
00:27:06,120 --> 00:27:07,840
Raise your hands.

385
00:27:14,280 --> 00:27:16,640
Here, tie the sarong like this.

386
00:27:25,440 --> 00:27:26,440
Done.

387
00:27:29,280 --> 00:27:30,360
Hey.

388
00:27:33,240 --> 00:27:34,480
What do I do next?

389
00:27:36,760 --> 00:27:38,920
Tell me when you’re done bathing,
I’ll wait here.

390
00:27:40,600 --> 00:27:42,640
How do I bathe?

391
00:27:54,240 --> 00:27:56,200
It’s like the tub at my house.

392
00:27:56,360 --> 00:27:57,480
And...

393
00:27:58,040 --> 00:27:59,760
how do I use soap?

394
00:28:00,200 --> 00:28:02,800
Just rub it inside like this.

395
00:28:04,760 --> 00:28:06,440
Inside the sarong.

396
00:28:09,120 --> 00:28:11,240
Why is this so complicated?

397
00:28:22,880 --> 00:28:25,160
-Hey.
-What?

398
00:28:25,520 --> 00:28:27,960
Can I get into the tub?

399
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:29,640
At home.

400
00:28:29,640 --> 00:28:31,640
-I soak in the tub.
-Hey, no.

401
00:28:31,680 --> 00:28:33,200
I haven’t bathed yet.

402
00:28:33,320 --> 00:28:34,720
You’ll make the water dirty.

403
00:28:37,480 --> 00:28:39,120
It’s way more comfortable like this.

404
00:28:39,360 --> 00:28:41,000
And it doesn’t make a mess either.

405
00:28:44,720 --> 00:28:46,360
I’ve got an idea!

406
00:28:59,800 --> 00:29:01,280
What are you doing?

407
00:29:02,520 --> 00:29:04,280
Let’s share the tub.

408
00:29:04,600 --> 00:29:07,160
We’re both wearing sarongs,
what are you shy about?

409
00:29:07,360 --> 00:29:09,200
You’re not shy, but I am.

410
00:29:18,160 --> 00:29:19,200
Come here.

411
00:29:23,320 --> 00:29:24,520
Hurry up.

412
00:29:24,920 --> 00:29:28,320
Wait, the tub is this small.

413
00:29:28,360 --> 00:29:30,360
Why squeeze in together?

414
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:35,000
I have something to confess.

415
00:30:35,760 --> 00:30:37,400
Confess what?

416
00:30:37,840 --> 00:30:39,960
It’s nothing serious.

417
00:30:40,120 --> 00:30:42,280
No need to look so shocked.

418
00:30:43,120 --> 00:30:44,880
Then just say it.

419
00:30:46,880 --> 00:30:49,000
Do you remember the first day we met?

420
00:30:50,560 --> 00:30:53,920
Back then, I wanted to beat you.

421
00:30:54,040 --> 00:30:56,480
Because you looked down on me.

422
00:30:57,440 --> 00:31:00,000
So I made that marriage proposal.

423
00:31:01,400 --> 00:31:02,600
But I think...

424
00:31:04,160 --> 00:31:05,960
I’ve changed my mind now.

425
00:31:06,320 --> 00:31:08,000
Changed your mind about what?

426
00:31:09,160 --> 00:31:10,840
Are you canceling the lease?

427
00:31:10,880 --> 00:31:13,480
Or not renewing it with me?

428
00:31:13,600 --> 00:31:14,880
No.

429
00:31:18,920 --> 00:31:20,000
I think...

430
00:31:22,800 --> 00:31:24,480
Actually...

431
00:31:32,560 --> 00:31:34,000
I like you.

432
00:31:41,560 --> 00:31:43,360
I liked you from the first day we met.

433
00:31:44,520 --> 00:31:47,840
And after seeing you cry last night.

434
00:31:48,280 --> 00:31:50,080
It made me realize...

435
00:31:51,680 --> 00:31:53,880
I want to be serious with you.

436
00:31:59,440 --> 00:32:00,920
I don’t want...

437
00:32:00,920 --> 00:32:03,880
our agreement to be just business.

438
00:32:06,480 --> 00:32:08,680
I want us to love each other.

439
00:32:10,400 --> 00:32:12,000
And get married.

440
00:32:13,760 --> 00:32:15,000
What do you think?

441
00:32:48,600 --> 00:32:50,680
Do we still miss each other?

442
00:33:00,360 --> 00:33:01,800
See you in Thailand.

443
00:33:01,840 --> 00:33:03,720
I’ll be back soon.

444
00:33:07,920 --> 00:33:10,240
(Jane)

445
00:33:25,600 --> 00:33:27,800
So what are we?

446
00:33:27,800 --> 00:33:30,400
I text you every day but you never reply.

447
00:33:30,440 --> 00:33:32,320
And then you reply with just this?

448
00:33:38,520 --> 00:33:40,080
Answer me, Jane.

449
00:33:55,960 --> 00:33:57,360
Why are you so quiet?

450
00:33:57,520 --> 00:33:59,880
You’d usually snap at me by now.

451
00:34:04,800 --> 00:34:06,520
I’m cold.

452
00:34:07,160 --> 00:34:09,080
I’m going inside.

453
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:43,920
Hey, wake up.

454
00:34:46,199 --> 00:34:48,239
Wake up, come on.

455
00:34:49,360 --> 00:34:50,639
No.

456
00:34:50,679 --> 00:34:53,840
If you don’t get up, I’ll carry you.

457
00:34:54,199 --> 00:34:55,719
What time is it?

458
00:34:55,760 --> 00:34:57,920
-It’s six.
-Is that 6 a.m. or 6 p.m.?

459
00:34:57,920 --> 00:34:59,240
Morning.

460
00:35:00,560 --> 00:35:02,680
-Let’s go make merit.
-I’m not going.

461
00:35:02,680 --> 00:35:04,440
Come on, earn some merit.

462
00:35:04,440 --> 00:35:06,040
No.

463
00:35:06,080 --> 00:35:08,440
I’m not earning anything.

464
00:35:08,480 --> 00:35:09,760
Let me stay sinful.

465
00:35:09,800 --> 00:35:12,240
-Come on, get up.
-I’m not going.

466
00:35:18,720 --> 00:35:20,040
I’m not going.

467
00:35:20,520 --> 00:35:22,720
-Don’t.
-Come on.

468
00:35:22,760 --> 00:35:23,760
Let’s go.

469
00:35:24,800 --> 00:35:28,240
No. I’m not going.

470
00:35:34,600 --> 00:35:35,640
Hey.

471
00:35:42,800 --> 00:35:44,560
Put the food in here.

472
00:35:50,760 --> 00:35:52,040
Add some sweets too.

473
00:36:02,920 --> 00:36:04,640
Receive the blessing.

474
00:36:05,360 --> 00:36:08,200
Abhivadana-silissa niccam.

475
00:36:08,240 --> 00:36:11,880
Vuddhapacayino jattaro dhammavaddhanti.

476
00:36:11,920 --> 00:36:14,440
Ayus, vanno, sukham.

477
00:36:14,440 --> 00:36:17,240
-Balam.
-Amen.

478
00:36:21,520 --> 00:36:24,440
The weather’s nice this morning,
want to take a walk?

479
00:36:26,280 --> 00:36:27,840
Where are you going?

480
00:36:29,400 --> 00:36:32,360
I’m sleepy, I’m going back to bed.

481
00:36:32,920 --> 00:36:35,480
If you don’t want to walk.

482
00:36:35,480 --> 00:36:38,000
I can take you on my motorbike.

483
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:39,760
You can look around.

484
00:36:39,800 --> 00:36:42,800
And get to know this place better.

485
00:36:45,200 --> 00:36:47,000
If you want to go, go alone.

486
00:36:47,000 --> 00:36:48,840
Stop forcing me.

487
00:36:59,160 --> 00:37:00,560
Hey.

488
00:37:00,560 --> 00:37:02,680
Drive carefully, I’m about to fall.

489
00:37:02,720 --> 00:37:04,400
Sorry, I didn’t see the pothole.

490
00:37:04,400 --> 00:37:06,880
Hold onto me, so you won’t fall.

491
00:37:15,200 --> 00:37:16,320
Hey.

492
00:37:16,320 --> 00:37:18,840
Don’t press your chest against my back.

493
00:37:19,600 --> 00:37:21,320
Look at the road.

494
00:37:23,400 --> 00:37:24,760
You idiot.

495
00:37:54,640 --> 00:37:57,560
Sit and enjoy the fresh countryside air.

496
00:37:57,600 --> 00:38:00,520
There’s definitely less dust here
than in Bangkok.

497
00:38:09,640 --> 00:38:11,040
Can you sit now?

498
00:38:26,840 --> 00:38:28,360
Do you like it here?

499
00:38:30,000 --> 00:38:32,320
It’s nice for a short stay.

500
00:38:32,360 --> 00:38:35,080
But I don’t know if...

501
00:38:35,120 --> 00:38:36,600
I don’t know if I can stay.

502
00:38:36,600 --> 00:38:37,920
I might get bored.

503
00:38:38,520 --> 00:38:40,960
There’s plenty to do here.

504
00:38:41,000 --> 00:38:42,800
If you get bored, just tell me.

505
00:38:42,840 --> 00:38:44,640
I’ll find something for you to do.

506
00:38:45,360 --> 00:38:47,560
Farming? No thanks.

507
00:38:47,600 --> 00:38:50,640
I don’t know how, and I don’t plan to.

508
00:38:56,280 --> 00:38:59,960
At first, when I didn’t renew
the mall lease for you.

509
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:03,840
It was because I wanted to build
an agricultural learning center in the city.

510
00:39:03,880 --> 00:39:06,920
I wanted people in Bangkok
to see the value of agriculture.

511
00:39:07,520 --> 00:39:10,720
And... I wanted local graduates
to have jobs too.

512
00:39:12,000 --> 00:39:14,840
But I’ve already canceled that project.

513
00:39:15,440 --> 00:39:17,360
Help me think about this.

514
00:39:17,920 --> 00:39:20,960
How can we help people here
earn a living?

515
00:39:23,440 --> 00:39:25,240
You’re quite kind-hearted.

516
00:39:26,680 --> 00:39:30,320
I have more than enough wealth for a lifetime.

517
00:39:30,840 --> 00:39:32,520
Might as well share some.

518
00:39:35,720 --> 00:39:37,600
By the way...

519
00:39:37,600 --> 00:39:40,320
Does all this land belong to you?

520
00:39:40,600 --> 00:39:42,360
I heard that...

521
00:39:42,400 --> 00:39:45,080
you still have several plots in the city.

522
00:39:45,080 --> 00:39:47,760
And every single one is prime location.

523
00:39:47,800 --> 00:39:48,800
Right?

524
00:39:50,600 --> 00:39:52,320
Your family is rich too.

525
00:39:52,320 --> 00:39:55,040
So why are you so obsessed with land?

526
00:39:56,000 --> 00:39:59,120
I’m not thinking
you’d take anything from me.

527
00:39:59,440 --> 00:40:00,560
I just...

528
00:40:00,720 --> 00:40:01,960
got curious.

529
00:40:02,320 --> 00:40:03,760
I know.

530
00:40:03,800 --> 00:40:06,360
But I wanted to know, so I asked.

531
00:40:06,360 --> 00:40:07,560
Just in case...

532
00:40:07,760 --> 00:40:09,160
let’s say...

533
00:40:09,680 --> 00:40:11,760
we really do get married.

534
00:40:11,800 --> 00:40:13,400
Whatever belongs to you.

535
00:40:13,440 --> 00:40:15,520
would also become mine, right?

536
00:40:15,560 --> 00:40:17,560
And whatever belongs to me.

537
00:40:17,760 --> 00:40:19,960
stays mine.

538
00:40:23,360 --> 00:40:24,640
That’s kind of weird, right?

539
00:40:25,720 --> 00:40:28,880
But anyway, whatever belongs to me.

540
00:40:28,920 --> 00:40:30,440
I’ll give it all to you.

541
00:40:31,000 --> 00:40:32,360
Really?

542
00:40:32,680 --> 00:40:33,760
Really.

543
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:39,360
But... can I ask you something?

544
00:40:39,760 --> 00:40:43,640
You can ask, but whether
I answer is another story.

545
00:40:43,840 --> 00:40:46,840
I see you staring at your phone all day.

546
00:40:46,920 --> 00:40:49,240
And yesterday, when we were bathing.

547
00:40:49,600 --> 00:40:51,800
Right after I said that.

548
00:40:51,800 --> 00:40:53,560
you looked at your phone.

549
00:40:54,200 --> 00:40:55,880
I want to ask...

550
00:40:55,880 --> 00:40:57,720
are you talking to someone?

551
00:41:02,320 --> 00:41:04,600
I’m a socialite, remember?

552
00:41:04,640 --> 00:41:06,960
Of course I’m always on my phone.

553
00:41:24,040 --> 00:41:25,040
Hey.

554
00:41:25,200 --> 00:41:26,760
Why are you grabbing my hand?

555
00:41:28,120 --> 00:41:30,040
Aren’t you pulling me up?

556
00:41:31,120 --> 00:41:32,480
No.

557
00:41:32,520 --> 00:41:34,640
I’m asking for the motorbike key.

558
00:41:34,680 --> 00:41:36,560
I’ll drive us back.

559
00:41:38,680 --> 00:41:40,560
You can ride a motorbike?

560
00:41:51,520 --> 00:41:53,360
Come on.

561
00:41:57,440 --> 00:41:59,160
Hey, hey.

562
00:42:01,520 --> 00:42:03,440
Can you actually ride?

563
00:42:03,480 --> 00:42:06,240
Of course. Don’t worry, but...

564
00:42:08,680 --> 00:42:11,320
whether I’ll crash is another story.

565
00:42:12,240 --> 00:42:14,200
Hey.

566
00:42:14,240 --> 00:42:15,920
Why are you holding my waist?

567
00:42:15,920 --> 00:42:18,000
I might fall.

568
00:42:18,040 --> 00:42:20,520
I can ride.

569
00:42:22,160 --> 00:42:24,400
-Don’t swerve.
-I’m not swerving.

570
00:42:24,440 --> 00:42:26,760
Look, the road is like that
all the way over there.

571
00:42:36,880 --> 00:42:39,640
You were gone for a bit and did all this?

572
00:42:39,720 --> 00:42:41,680
I prepared a full meal for you.

573
00:42:41,760 --> 00:42:44,680
As for the snakehead fish,
I caught it myself.

574
00:42:46,360 --> 00:42:47,800
I don’t want to praise you, but...

575
00:42:47,800 --> 00:42:50,040
is there anything you can’t do?

576
00:42:50,600 --> 00:42:53,480
Well... what I can’t do?

577
00:42:53,480 --> 00:42:55,840
I guess I’m not really your girlfriend yet.

578
00:42:57,000 --> 00:43:00,240
Just your business girlfriend.

579
00:43:01,240 --> 00:43:02,720
You’re bringing that up again.

580
00:43:05,880 --> 00:43:07,840
If you’re not ready to answer, it’s okay.

581
00:43:07,880 --> 00:43:09,400
I won’t pressure you.

582
00:43:09,600 --> 00:43:11,040
I can wait.

583
00:43:22,720 --> 00:43:23,960
By the way...

584
00:43:25,120 --> 00:43:27,240
Where is your assistant today?

585
00:43:27,280 --> 00:43:28,760
He’s been gone all day.

586
00:43:28,760 --> 00:43:30,080
He’s at home.

587
00:43:30,120 --> 00:43:32,000
On days he has dialysis.

588
00:43:32,000 --> 00:43:33,640
He doesn’t feel too well.

589
00:43:35,880 --> 00:43:37,840
Will he be okay?

590
00:43:39,000 --> 00:43:40,320
He’s holding on.

591
00:43:40,600 --> 00:43:42,440
But who knows for how long.

592
00:43:43,520 --> 00:43:45,440
Is it that serious?

593
00:43:46,120 --> 00:43:47,760
I feel bad for him.

594
00:43:48,880 --> 00:43:51,320
I’ll be nicer to him then.

595
00:43:51,320 --> 00:43:53,360
As long as he doesn’t mess with me first.

596
00:43:54,720 --> 00:43:56,960
He’s come to terms with it.

597
00:43:57,800 --> 00:43:59,120
Come to terms with what?

598
00:43:59,160 --> 00:44:01,560
He still asks me for money every day.

599
00:44:03,400 --> 00:44:06,280
He gets free treatment at a public hospital.

600
00:44:06,320 --> 00:44:08,240
Every bit of money he earns.

601
00:44:08,280 --> 00:44:10,120
He donates it all to the hospital.

602
00:44:26,520 --> 00:44:28,000
Here, take it.

603
00:44:32,200 --> 00:44:33,960
So what are you doing today?

604
00:44:35,120 --> 00:44:37,480
I’m taking Pidpee and Muedmon
to play in the mud.

605
00:44:37,520 --> 00:44:39,040
It’s getting hot.

606
00:44:39,720 --> 00:44:40,960
I’m coming too.

607
00:44:42,800 --> 00:44:45,240
You’re going in that outfit?

608
00:44:47,080 --> 00:44:48,360
Why, what’s wrong with it?

609
00:44:52,280 --> 00:44:53,480
Done.

610
00:45:00,240 --> 00:45:01,880
Why are you smiling?

611
00:45:02,600 --> 00:45:04,480
Is it really that ugly?

612
00:45:04,520 --> 00:45:06,720
I think... this just isn’t me.

613
00:45:06,720 --> 00:45:07,720
I should go change.

614
00:45:07,760 --> 00:45:09,080
Wait.

615
00:45:10,920 --> 00:45:12,200
Someone like you.

616
00:45:12,240 --> 00:45:13,800
looks beautiful in anything.

617
00:45:17,520 --> 00:45:19,240
I’ve been wanting to ask you.

618
00:45:19,280 --> 00:45:22,920
That... 1888.

619
00:45:22,920 --> 00:45:24,640
What does it mean?

620
00:45:24,680 --> 00:45:26,120
It’s a fertilizer formula.

621
00:45:26,160 --> 00:45:29,200
Oh, I thought it was something special.

622
00:45:30,520 --> 00:45:32,760
Do you know, the number 18.

623
00:45:32,760 --> 00:45:34,880
is my personal number.

624
00:45:35,240 --> 00:45:36,360
What number?

625
00:45:36,600 --> 00:45:37,880
A lucky number?

626
00:45:38,720 --> 00:45:40,560
It’s not like that at all.

627
00:45:40,720 --> 00:45:42,800
Come here, I’ll show you.

628
00:45:45,160 --> 00:45:46,280
Let me borrow this.

629
00:45:48,920 --> 00:45:50,000
Look.

630
00:45:55,480 --> 00:45:56,480
Here.

631
00:45:59,360 --> 00:46:00,480
What do you mean?

632
00:46:03,360 --> 00:46:05,080
It really says Si.

633
00:46:05,120 --> 00:46:06,760
Yeah.

634
00:46:09,000 --> 00:46:11,480
Then... I’ll keep this.

635
00:46:12,120 --> 00:46:13,760
What are you going to do with it?

636
00:46:14,280 --> 00:46:15,280
Not telling.

637
00:46:17,240 --> 00:46:21,040
Come on, Pidpee and Muedmon
must be burning up by now.

638
00:46:22,880 --> 00:46:24,160
I can walk.

639
00:46:24,160 --> 00:46:26,200
No need to sneak a feel.

640
00:46:36,480 --> 00:46:39,360
Come on, Pidpee,
let’s go soak in the mud.

641
00:46:39,360 --> 00:46:41,080
It’s too hot.

642
00:46:41,240 --> 00:46:43,080
Walk faster.

643
00:46:43,440 --> 00:46:46,200
In weather like this.

644
00:46:46,440 --> 00:46:48,760
We have to soak in the mud.

645
00:46:50,440 --> 00:46:51,840
What’s this?

646
00:46:51,840 --> 00:46:53,680
Their poop.

647
00:46:54,520 --> 00:46:56,680
Good thing you didn’t step on it.

648
00:46:57,200 --> 00:46:58,200
Come on.

649
00:46:59,040 --> 00:47:00,800
We’re here.

650
00:47:02,840 --> 00:47:04,600
Go ahead.

651
00:47:12,480 --> 00:47:14,400
Feels good, right?

652
00:47:17,720 --> 00:47:18,800
Hey.

653
00:47:19,320 --> 00:47:20,840
Your cheeks are all red.

654
00:47:20,880 --> 00:47:22,800
It’s the sun.

655
00:47:22,840 --> 00:47:26,000
I’m not a robot to stay in the heat all day.

656
00:47:27,280 --> 00:47:28,760
What song is that?

657
00:47:28,800 --> 00:47:30,600
It’s already hot as it is.

658
00:47:30,960 --> 00:47:32,840
It’s a trending TikTok song.

659
00:47:32,880 --> 00:47:35,000
Jiw’s been singing it all day.

660
00:47:39,760 --> 00:47:41,280
Take my hat.

661
00:47:47,160 --> 00:47:50,000
With sun this strong, will I get melasma?

662
00:47:50,440 --> 00:47:52,880
That’s just how the weather is.

663
00:47:55,040 --> 00:47:58,120
I just released water from the pond into the field.

664
00:47:58,160 --> 00:48:01,080
Want to catch some fish together?

665
00:48:01,720 --> 00:48:04,720
No, don’t drag me into something weird.

666
00:48:04,720 --> 00:48:06,000
I’m not playing with you.

667
00:48:06,320 --> 00:48:08,800
Then... just watch me.

668
00:48:09,320 --> 00:48:12,000
Like I have a choice.

669
00:48:13,680 --> 00:48:15,080
Come on.

670
00:48:17,600 --> 00:48:19,640
What are you doing, walking back and forth?

671
00:48:19,680 --> 00:48:21,720
It feels refreshing.

672
00:48:27,040 --> 00:48:29,680
This one’s as big as my leg, hurry.

673
00:48:29,680 --> 00:48:32,440
Wait, I can’t be in two places at once.

674
00:48:32,480 --> 00:48:34,000
Come on.

675
00:48:35,280 --> 00:48:38,240
There’s one behind you, as big as my arm.

676
00:48:38,240 --> 00:48:40,400
It swam over there, quick, that one.

677
00:48:40,440 --> 00:48:42,120
-Hey.
-See it? It’s jumping.

678
00:48:42,120 --> 00:48:44,240
I haven’t even caught the last one.

679
00:48:44,240 --> 00:48:46,200
Well...

680
00:48:46,240 --> 00:48:47,720
if you want it.

681
00:48:47,760 --> 00:48:49,480
come help me.

682
00:48:50,280 --> 00:48:51,480
No.

683
00:48:51,680 --> 00:48:54,080
The mud is dirty, I don’t like it.

684
00:48:56,200 --> 00:48:58,560
It’s not that dirty.

685
00:48:58,600 --> 00:49:00,400
And it washes off.

686
00:49:08,880 --> 00:49:10,080
Hey...

687
00:49:10,720 --> 00:49:12,200
come help me.

688
00:49:16,480 --> 00:49:18,800
There’s another fish there, look.

689
00:49:18,840 --> 00:49:20,000
Hey...

690
00:49:20,240 --> 00:49:21,720
If you want to help me.

691
00:49:21,760 --> 00:49:22,920
then come down.

692
00:49:22,960 --> 00:49:24,240
Don’t boss me around.

693
00:49:24,240 --> 00:49:25,400
I’m tired.

694
00:49:25,440 --> 00:49:28,040
Then... come take this first.

695
00:49:28,040 --> 00:49:29,480
Bring the basket too.

696
00:49:31,200 --> 00:49:32,280
This?

697
00:49:34,600 --> 00:49:36,560
Careful, it’s slippery.

698
00:49:49,960 --> 00:49:53,400
I told you, it’s slippery.

699
00:49:55,560 --> 00:49:56,720
Here.

700
00:49:59,480 --> 00:50:02,000
Take this, now it’s your turn to catch fish.

701
00:50:13,080 --> 00:50:14,720
Hey.

702
00:50:14,760 --> 00:50:17,040
I caught one, come look.

703
00:50:17,080 --> 00:50:18,760
It’s bigger than the last one.

704
00:50:18,760 --> 00:50:20,800
Did you catch any?

705
00:50:23,400 --> 00:50:25,200
Not bad.

706
00:50:34,560 --> 00:50:35,680
Hey.

707
00:50:36,560 --> 00:50:38,400
Don’t let it happen again.

708
00:50:48,400 --> 00:50:49,600
Hey.

709
00:50:50,240 --> 00:50:52,160
What’s wrong with you?

710
00:50:52,440 --> 00:50:53,880
Did something get in your eye?

711
00:50:53,880 --> 00:50:57,400
-Let me see.
-My eye stings, take a look.

712
00:50:57,920 --> 00:51:00,680
Is there... mud in it?

713
00:51:04,320 --> 00:51:05,840
Let me see the other eye.

714
00:51:05,840 --> 00:51:07,800
Look carefully.

715
00:51:14,840 --> 00:51:16,400
You’re messing with me.

716
00:51:17,840 --> 00:51:20,480
If I’d known, I’d splash mud into your eyes for real.

717
00:51:21,240 --> 00:51:23,880
-I’m leaving.
-Hey.

718
00:51:24,200 --> 00:51:25,240
Bring the fish up too.

719
00:51:25,280 --> 00:51:26,560
I’m done playing with you.

720
00:51:26,560 --> 00:51:27,800
It’s so hot.

721
00:51:27,840 --> 00:51:29,160
Wait for me.

722
00:51:29,200 --> 00:51:31,280
I’m not waiting, I’m hot.

723
00:51:31,360 --> 00:51:32,440
Hey.

724
00:51:33,000 --> 00:51:34,680
Do you want grilled fish?

725
00:51:34,760 --> 00:51:35,960
This one?

726
00:51:37,760 --> 00:51:39,120
Sounds interesting.

727
00:51:39,160 --> 00:51:40,400
You’re going to cook it?

728
00:51:41,360 --> 00:51:42,480
Sure.

729
00:51:53,760 --> 00:51:55,360
-Is it even edible?
-Here it is.

730
00:51:55,400 --> 00:51:56,880
Of course it is.

731
00:52:00,720 --> 00:52:02,600
Here, I’ll peel it for you.

732
00:52:07,800 --> 00:52:09,240
This is so delicious.

733
00:52:09,880 --> 00:52:11,440
Maybe it’s just me.

734
00:52:11,480 --> 00:52:13,320
But fish we catch ourselves.

735
00:52:13,360 --> 00:52:15,080
tastes extra good.

736
00:52:15,200 --> 00:52:16,720
You’re not imagining it.

737
00:52:16,760 --> 00:52:19,120
Anything we do ourselves.

738
00:52:19,160 --> 00:52:21,200
always feels more special.

739
00:52:22,120 --> 00:52:25,000
Come to think of it, I’m pretty capable.

740
00:52:26,080 --> 00:52:28,680
-Here, have some more. It’s good.
-Okay.

741
00:52:31,440 --> 00:52:33,680
If we had seafood dipping sauce.

742
00:52:33,720 --> 00:52:34,880
it would be perfect.

743
00:52:35,560 --> 00:52:37,000
Try some.

744
00:52:39,240 --> 00:52:40,400
Is it good?

745
00:52:41,040 --> 00:52:42,480
I caught this one.

746
00:52:44,960 --> 00:52:46,080
Yours is over there.

747
00:52:46,120 --> 00:52:47,360
Go check it.

748
00:53:21,360 --> 00:53:23,440
I think it’s burnt.

749
00:53:24,080 --> 00:53:25,200
Hey...

750
00:53:25,440 --> 00:53:27,320
want to go rinse off over there?

751
00:53:28,040 --> 00:53:29,520
Rinse off?

752
00:53:30,520 --> 00:53:33,680
We just walked back from there.

753
00:53:42,000 --> 00:53:43,560
Who would’ve thought.

754
00:53:43,600 --> 00:53:46,200
someone like me would be doing this.

755
00:53:46,560 --> 00:53:49,200
Well... it’s something new.

756
00:53:49,240 --> 00:53:50,680
Do you like it?

757
00:53:51,520 --> 00:53:52,680
Well...

758
00:53:53,440 --> 00:53:54,720
I like it.

759
00:53:54,760 --> 00:53:56,080
It’s peaceful here.

760
00:53:56,120 --> 00:53:57,200
And...

761
00:53:57,640 --> 00:53:59,200
it’s fun doing things.

762
00:53:59,200 --> 00:54:02,800
But if I had to choose, I still prefer Bangkok.

763
00:54:04,200 --> 00:54:07,280
At least you don’t hate it here.

764
00:54:11,640 --> 00:54:13,160
The mud here is really sticky.

765
00:54:13,200 --> 00:54:15,040
I’ve washed ten times and it’s still there.

766
00:54:15,040 --> 00:54:16,280
Come, I’ll help you.

767
00:54:54,320 --> 00:54:55,880
There’s some on your neck too.

768
00:55:24,560 --> 00:55:25,680
Hey.

769
00:55:27,200 --> 00:55:28,880
Don’t cross the line.

770
00:55:32,360 --> 00:55:33,880
Hey, hey.

771
00:56:19,760 --> 00:56:22,080
Hold me tight
and rest your head on my shoulder.

772
00:56:22,120 --> 00:56:23,120
Hurry.

773
00:56:23,680 --> 00:56:25,400
You idiot, you perv.

774
00:56:25,440 --> 00:56:26,440
If...

775
00:56:26,720 --> 00:56:29,000
you can walk straight to me.

776
00:56:29,120 --> 00:56:30,200
I’ll let you kiss me.

777
00:56:34,040 --> 00:56:35,040
You crazy girl.

778
00:56:35,080 --> 00:56:37,000
How can you sleep when you’re this dirty?

779
00:56:40,280 --> 00:56:41,280
What are you doing?

780
00:56:41,360 --> 00:56:44,160
Can’t I hug my girlfriend when I miss her?

781
00:56:44,720 --> 00:56:46,200
Have you ever...

782
00:56:46,240 --> 00:56:48,680
had any bad thoughts about me?

783
00:56:48,840 --> 00:56:50,000
Right now...

784
00:56:50,120 --> 00:56:51,560
I am.

785
00:56:55,640 --> 00:56:56,920
(Switch to racing mode)

786
00:56:57,480 --> 00:56:59,400
- Van.
- Where are you going?

787
00:56:59,440 --> 00:57:01,880
- Don’t rush walking.
- You’ll trip and fall

788
00:57:01,880 --> 00:57:04,520
- because you’re looking at me, not the road.
- Tang, Tang.

789
00:57:04,520 --> 00:57:06,160
Tang, bring me my slippers.
(Actually tripped)

790
00:57:07,120 --> 00:57:07,800
Damn it.

791
00:57:07,800 --> 00:57:08,720
Hey, how is it?

792
00:57:11,720 --> 00:57:13,160
Wait, twist it back a bit.

793
00:57:13,160 --> 00:57:14,640
- Yes, yes.
- Yes, like that.

794
00:57:14,680 --> 00:57:15,680
- Here.
- Right here.

795
00:57:16,280 --> 00:57:18,520
The light isn’t necessary, remove it.

796
00:57:19,200 --> 00:57:21,280
- Is this okay, P’?
- Yes, this angle.

797
00:57:21,280 --> 00:57:22,680
- Opposite this box.
- It’s shaking.

798
00:57:22,680 --> 00:57:23,720
It’s shaking.

799
00:57:23,760 --> 00:57:25,320
- No, it’s not.
- Okay.
